  <prompt>Author a NEW `EntityNameValidatorNodeExecutor.cs` in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/`, mirroring the pattern of the sibling `LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutor.cs`. Inputs: `{candidateText, allowList[]}`. Outputs: `{scrubbedText, removedTerms[]}`. Per-removal, log a structured `hallucination_detected` event via ILogger. Then author `EntityNameValidatorNodeExecutorTests.cs` at `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/`, mirroring `LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutorTests.cs`, with the 5 required tests below.</prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. BFF AI NodeExecutor author with deep knowledge of the post-LLM scrubbing pattern, the Singleton-with-Scoped-dependency DI convention, and xUnit fixture authoring conventions.</role>

  <goal>Two new files exist: (a) production NodeExecutor implementing Validate + ExecuteAsync against the input contract above; (b) xUnit test file with all 5 required tests passing. `dotnet test` succeeds. `dotnet build` succeeds. Publish-size delta ≤ +0.2 MB.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>R4 FR-3 (lines 116-122) ships post-LLM output scrubbing as defense-in-depth against AI hallucination. R3 UAT confirmed grounding alone is insufficient: the LLM emitted fictional firm names ("Johnson &amp; Lee LLP", "Davis v. Metro Transit") even when prompt instructions said "use only names from input." This NodeExecutor compares LLM output text against an explicit allow-list built from input payload; sentences mentioning entities not in the list are removed; each removal is logged for monitoring. AC-3b mandates the xUnit test scrubs "Johnson &amp; Lee LLP" when not in allow-list AND emits the hallucination_detected event.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutor.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/QueryDataverseNodeExecutor.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/INodeExecutor.cs</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutorTests.cs</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/spec.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <justification>
    <existing>The closest existing surface is `LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutor.cs` (sibling NodeExecutor pattern, also ActionType-anchored). Survey of `Services/Ai/Nodes/` shows no current post-LLM output-scrubbing executor — verified via Grep for "scrub" / "validate.*name" / "hallucinat" in the Nodes folder (zero hits).</existing>
    <extension>No — LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutor performs INPUT lookup (queries Dataverse for user memberships); EntityNameValidator performs OUTPUT scrubbing (post-process LLM text against allow-list). The responsibilities and DI dependencies are fundamentally different (Dataverse client vs string analysis only). Extending the existing executor would conflate input-resolution and output-validation responsibilities; this fails the Single Responsibility Principle and violates the node-executor-authoring pattern.</extension>
    <cost-of-doing-nothing>Concrete failure mode: R3 UAT verified the LLM emits hallucinated entity names (Johnson &amp; Lee LLP, Davis v. Metro Transit) into the narration output, even with grounding instructions in the prompt. Without this executor, those names reach the widget and the user perceives the AI as fabricating client data. Grounding + temperature 0 alone are demonstrably insufficient (verified by R3 UAT trace).</cost-of-doing-nothing>
  </justification>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">All AI logic in BFF; new NodeExecutor extends established framework — no facade-layer extraction needed (executor is internal to AI orchestration).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI Minimalism — register via existing NodeExecutorModule extension; no new DI module.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10">BFF Hygiene — verify publish-size delta + CVE check + bff-extensions.md §A checklist. Expected delta ≤ +0.2 MB.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec AC-3b">xUnit test passes — input with "Johnson &amp; Lee LLP" (not in allow-list) → output has it removed AND warning event emitted.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Mandatory tests: Validate_MissingCandidateText, Validate_MissingAllowList, ExecuteAsync_ScrubsHallucination, ExecuteAsync_AllowListPassThrough, ExecuteAsync_EmitsHallucinationEventPerRemoval.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Per-removal structured log event MUST use the literal key `hallucination_detected` (App Insights query target per docs/guides/AI-MONITORING-DASHBOARD.md).</constraint>
  </constraints>

