  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load all knowledge files. Read spec.md FR-3 (lines 116-122) + AC-3b. Verify task 002 enum value is committed (EntityNameValidator = 141).</step>
    <step order="2">Read `LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutor.cs` end-to-end to understand the class shape: namespace, base class / interface, constructor DI (logger), Validate(), ExecuteAsync(), input/output node-data conventions.</step>
    <step order="3">Read `LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutorTests.cs` end-to-end to understand the test fixture pattern: Mock&lt;ILogger&gt;, arrange/act/assert layout, how Validate tests assert error messages, how ExecuteAsync tests build NodeContext.</step>
    <step order="4">Author `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/EntityNameValidatorNodeExecutor.cs`: implement Validate (require candidateText non-null, allowList non-null), implement ExecuteAsync (sentence-level scan; if a sentence mentions a token not in allowList, remove that sentence; log `hallucination_detected` with structured properties `{removedTerm, sentence, allowListSize}`; return `{scrubbedText, removedTerms[]}`).</step>
    <step order="5">Register the new executor in the existing NodeExecutorModule (or equivalent DI registration block used by LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutor). Confirm no new DI module needed.</step>
    <step order="6">Author `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/EntityNameValidatorNodeExecutorTests.cs` with the 5 required tests: Validate_MissingCandidateText (asserts validation error); Validate_MissingAllowList (asserts validation error); ExecuteAsync_ScrubsHallucination (input "Acme Corp filed a brief. Johnson &amp; Lee LLP responded." with allowList=["Acme Corp"]; assert output contains "Acme Corp" and NOT "Johnson &amp; Lee LLP"); ExecuteAsync_AllowListPassThrough (all names in allow-list → scrubbedText == candidateText); ExecuteAsync_EmitsHallucinationEventPerRemoval (verify Mock&lt;ILogger&gt; received `hallucination_detected` event exactly once per removed term).</step>
    <step order="7">Run `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` filtered to EntityNameValidator — all 5 tests pass.</step>
    <step order="8">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="9">Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`; measure compressed delta; record vs baseline (~45.65 MB).</step>
    <step order="10">Run `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` — no new HIGH-severity CVE.</step>
    <step order="11">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change this task's status to ✅.</step>
    <step order="12">If deviations from plan, document in projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/notes/.</step>
  </steps>

